вҠў program-A
  given В§weighted-sum-A вүЎ "(cell definition: вҠў weighted-sum-A в–ё crystallized ...)"
  given В§total-weight-A вүЎ "(cell definition: вҠў total-weight-A в–ё crystallized ...)"
  given В§weighted-average-A вүЎ "(cell definition: вҠў weighted-average-A в–ё crystallized ...)"
  yield В§program-A-cells[], execution-order-A

  вҲҙ Assemble program A as a list of cell definitions.
    Execution order: input-data, weighted-sum-A, total-weight-A, weighted-average-A.
    The key: weighted-sum-A is scheduled BEFORE total-weight-A.
    Both depend only on input-data, so either could go first -- this ordering
    is one valid topological sort.

    Output execution-order-A вүЎ ["input-data", "weighted-sum-A", "total-weight-A", "weighted-average-A"]

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The LLM reads the three В§ definitions, confirms they form a diamond-shaped
-- dependency graph (input-data вҶ’ {weighted-sum-A, total-weight-A} вҶ’ weighted-average-A),
-- and assembles the sum-first topological sort.

  yield В§program-A-cells[] вүЎ [В§weighted-sum-A, В§total-weight-A, В§weighted-average-A]
  yield execution-order-A вүЎ ["input-data", "weighted-sum-A", "total-weight-A", "weighted-average-A"]

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ execution-order-A is a valid topological sort вҶ’ вң“
--     input-data has no deps (first is valid).
--     weighted-sum-A depends on input-data (appears after input-data вң“).
--     total-weight-A depends on input-data (appears after input-data вң“).
--     weighted-average-A depends on weighted-sum-A and total-weight-A (appears after both вң“).
--   вҠЁ weighted-sum-A appears before total-weight-A in execution-order-A вҶ’ вң“
--     (index 1 < index 2)
