-- frame 11: build-correspondence (hard cell, deterministic вҠў= evaluation)
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў build-correspondence в–ё crystallized
  given trace-AвҶ’final-state-A вүЎ { input-dataвҶ’values: [10,20,30,40], input-dataвҶ’weights: [1,2,3,4], weighted-sum-AвҶ’weighted-sum: 300, total-weight-AвҶ’total-weight: 10, weighted-average-AвҶ’average: 30 }
  given trace-BвҶ’final-state-B вүЎ { input-dataвҶ’values: [10,20,30,40], input-dataвҶ’weights: [1,2,3,4], total-weight-BвҶ’total-weight: 10, weighted-sum-BвҶ’weighted-sum: 300, weighted-average-BвҶ’average: 30 }
  yield correspondence[], matched-count, unmatched[]

  вҠў= correspondence вҶҗ [
    { cell-A: "weighted-sum-A",     cell-B: "weighted-sum-B",     field: "weighted-sum", match: final-state-AвҶ’weighted-sum-AвҶ’weighted-sum = final-state-BвҶ’weighted-sum-BвҶ’weighted-sum },
    { cell-A: "total-weight-A",     cell-B: "total-weight-B",     field: "total-weight", match: final-state-AвҶ’total-weight-AвҶ’total-weight = final-state-BвҶ’total-weight-BвҶ’total-weight },
    { cell-A: "weighted-average-A", cell-B: "weighted-average-B", field: "average",      match: final-state-AвҶ’weighted-average-AвҶ’average = final-state-BвҶ’weighted-average-BвҶ’average }
  ]

  вҠў= matched-count вҶҗ count(correspondence, c -> cвҶ’match = true)
  вҠў= unmatched вҶҗ filter(correspondence, c -> cвҶ’match = false)

-- Deterministic evaluation:
--   correspondence[0].match: 300 = 300 вҶ’ true
--   correspondence[1].match: 10 = 10 вҶ’ true
--   correspondence[2].match: 30 = 30 вҶ’ true
--   matched-count: count([true, true, true]) = 3
--   unmatched: filter([...], match=false) = []

  yield correspondence вүЎ [
    { cell-A: "weighted-sum-A",     cell-B: "weighted-sum-B",     field: "weighted-sum", match: true },
    { cell-A: "total-weight-A",     cell-B: "total-weight-B",     field: "total-weight", match: true },
    { cell-A: "weighted-average-A", cell-B: "weighted-average-B", field: "average",      match: true }
  ]
  yield matched-count вүЎ 3
  yield unmatched вүЎ []

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ len(correspondence) = 3 вҶ’ вң“ (3 = 3)
--   вҠЁ matched-count + len(unmatched) = len(correspondence) вҶ’ вң“ (3 + 0 = 3)
--
-- All oracles pass. Cell frozen.
-- Ready set after: { compare-execution-order }
-- (generate-proof still blocked: needs compare-execution-orderвҶ’*)

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 12: compare-execution-order (soft cell, LLM evaluation)
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў compare-execution-order
  given trace-AвҶ’frames-A вүЎ [
    { step: 0, cell: "input-data", ... },
    { step: 1, cell: "weighted-sum-A", ... },
    { step: 2, cell: "total-weight-A", ... },
    { step: 3, cell: "weighted-average-A", ... }
  ]
  given trace-BвҶ’frames-B вүЎ [
    { step: 0, cell: "input-data", ... },
    { step: 1, cell: "total-weight-B", ... },
    { step: 2, cell: "weighted-sum-B", ... },
    { step: 3, cell: "weighted-average-B", ... }
  ]
  yield order-differs, shared-steps[], divergence-point

  вҲҙ Compare the step-by-step execution order of В«trace-AвҶ’frames-AВ» and
    В«trace-BвҶ’frames-BВ».

    Identify:
    - shared-steps: cells that appear in the same position in both traces
      (e.g., input-data is step 0 in both)
    - divergence-point: the first step where the two traces evaluate
      different cells (step 1: sum-A vs weight-B)
    - order-differs: true if any steps evaluate different cells

    This establishes that the programs really DID execute in different orders,
    which is the precondition for the confluence proof to be meaningful.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- Step-by-step comparison of the two traces:
--   Step 0: A="input-data",        B="input-data"         вҶ’ SAME (shared)
--   Step 1: A="weighted-sum-A",    B="total-weight-B"     вҶ’ DIFFERENT (divergence!)
--   Step 2: A="total-weight-A",    B="weighted-sum-B"     вҶ’ DIFFERENT
--   Step 3: A="weighted-average-A" B="weighted-average-B"  вҶ’ same role, different name
-- The divergence occurs at step 1. Steps 1 and 2 are swapped between A and B.
-- This is the diamond: two independent cells evaluated in opposite order.

  yield order-differs вүЎ true
  yield shared-steps вүЎ [
    { step: 0, cell-A: "input-data", cell-B: "input-data" }
  ]
  yield divergence-point вүЎ 1

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ order-differs = true вҶ’ вң“
--   вҠЁ divergence-point <= len(trace-AвҶ’frames-A) вҶ’ вң“ (1 <= 4)
--   вҠЁ len(shared-steps) < len(trace-AвҶ’frames-A) вҶ’ вң“ (1 < 4)
--
-- All oracles pass. Cell frozen.
-- Ready set after: { generate-proof }
-- (generate-proof now has all deps: build-correspondenceвҶ’* вң“, compare-execution-orderвҶ’* вң“)

-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ
-- frame 13: generate-proof (soft cell, LLM evaluation вҖ” formal proof)
-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў generate-proof
  given build-correspondenceвҶ’correspondence вүЎ [
    { cell-A: "weighted-sum-A",     cell-B: "weighted-sum-B",     field: "weighted-sum", match: true },
    { cell-A: "total-weight-A",     cell-B: "total-weight-B",     field: "total-weight", match: true },
    { cell-A: "weighted-average-A", cell-B: "weighted-average-B", field: "average",      match: true }
  ]
  given build-correspondenceвҶ’matched-count вүЎ 3
  given build-correspondenceвҶ’unmatched вүЎ []
  given compare-execution-orderвҶ’order-differs вүЎ true
  given compare-execution-orderвҶ’divergence-point вүЎ 1
  yield proof-argument, proof-steps[], proof-technique

  вҲҙ Generate a formal equivalence proof for programs A and B.

    The proof has three parts:

    1. **Dependency isomorphism**: Show the dependency graphs of A and B are
       isomorphic. Both have the same shape: input-data feeds two independent
       cells (weighted-sum and total-weight), which feed into one final cell
       (weighted-average). The cell names differ but the graph structure is
       identical.

    2. **Cell-wise equivalence**: For each pair in В«build-correspondenceвҶ’correspondenceВ»,
       show that the cell bodies compute the same function. Since all paired cells
       are crystallized (вҠў=) with identical expressions, this is syntactic equality
       of the вҠў= bodies modulo renaming.

    3. **Confluence application**: By Cell's confluence theorem (eval_diamond),
       if two execution orders are both valid topological sorts of the same
       dependency graph, and all cells compute the same function, then the
       final states are identical. The divergence at step В«compare-execution-orderвҶ’divergence-pointВ»
       involves two independent cells -- exactly the diamond scenario.

    proof-technique вүЎ "structural induction on dependency graph + confluence theorem"

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The LLM constructs the three-part proof using the concrete data from
-- build-correspondence and compare-execution-order.

  yield proof-argument вүЎ "EQUIVALENCE PROOF: Programs A and B over weighted-average computation.

PART 1 вҖ” DEPENDENCY ISOMORPHISM:
Both programs share the same dependency graph shape:
  input-data вҶ’ { X, Y } вҶ’ weighted-average
where X and Y are independent cells computing weighted-sum and total-weight respectively. In program A, X=weighted-sum-A and Y=total-weight-A. In program B, X=total-weight-B and Y=weighted-sum-B. The graph is isomorphic under the renaming {weighted-sum-A вҶ” weighted-sum-B, total-weight-A вҶ” total-weight-B, weighted-average-A вҶ” weighted-average-B}. Both X and Y depend ONLY on input-data. Neither depends on the other. This independence is the structural precondition for confluence.

PART 2 вҖ” CELL-WISE EQUIVALENCE:
For each pair in the correspondence:
  (a) weighted-sum-A vs weighted-sum-B: both compute вҠў= sum(map(zip(values, weights), pair -> pair[0] * pair[1])). Syntactically identical вҠў= bodies. Same inputs (input-dataвҶ’values, input-dataвҶ’weights). Therefore identical functions.
  (b) total-weight-A vs total-weight-B: both compute вҠў= sum(weights). Syntactically identical. Same input (input-dataвҶ’weights). Identical functions.
  (c) weighted-average-A vs weighted-average-B: both compute вҠў= weighted-sum / total-weight. Syntactically identical. Inputs are the outputs of paired cells from (a) and (b). Given (a) and (b) produce identical values, (c) produces identical values.
All three pairs matched with equal outputs (verified empirically: 300=300, 10=10, 30=30).

PART 3 вҖ” CONFLUENCE APPLICATION:
Programs A and B are two topological sorts of the same dependency graph. They diverge at step 1 (divergence-point=1): A evaluates weighted-sum-A while B evaluates total-weight-B. These two cells are independent (neither depends on the other's output вҖ” both depend only on input-data). This is precisely the diamond scenario of Cell's eval_diamond theorem: when two independent cells are ready simultaneously, evaluating either first yields the same final state. The theorem guarantees that the scheduling difference at step 1 (and consequently step 2) cannot affect the final frozen state. QED."

  yield proof-steps вүЎ [
    "dependency-isomorphism: graphs are isomorphic under cell renaming, independent pair {X,Y} identified",
    "cell-equivalence: all three cell pairs have syntactically identical вҠў= bodies, confirmed by 3/3 match in correspondence",
    "confluence-application: divergence at step 1 involves independent cells, eval_diamond theorem applies, final states guaranteed identical"
  ]

  yield proof-technique вүЎ "structural induction on dependency graph + confluence theorem"

