вҠў= obs-false-crystallization-fix
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "v0.2 FALSE CRYSTALLIZATION FIXED: R16's verify-proof was a single вҠў= cell using missing-from() and semantic predicates like 'proof-technique contains confluence' вҖ” neither valid in the v0.2 expression language. R17 splits it into verify-proof-structure (hard, uses only len/count/comparison/boolean вҖ” all v0.2 primitives) and verify-proof-semantics (soft, honestly uses LLM to check whether proof-steps cover the three required concepts). This is the crystallization boundary rule in action: if it requires interpretation, it belongs in a soft cell. The v0.2 вҠў= expression language audit caught exactly the anti-pattern the spec warned about."

вҠў= obs-confluence-made-concrete
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "CONFLUENCE MADE CONCRETE: This program doesn't just CLAIM confluence вҖ” it DEMONSTRATES it. Two programs with identical cell bodies but different schedules produce identical frozen states (300, 10, 30 in both traces). The proof links this to eval_diamond in Lean. The execution trace itself shows the property: frames 3-5 (A: sumвҶ’weightвҶ’average) and frames 6-8 (B: weightвҶ’sumвҶ’average) produce the same values in different order. Cell's theoretical property becomes empirically verifiable."

вҠў= obs-hard-soft-balance
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "HARD/SOFT BALANCE IS 50/50: 8 hard cells (arithmetic, structural checks) and 8 soft cells (assembly, tracing, proof generation, gap analysis, certificate). This reflects the program's nature: the COMPUTATION is deterministic (weighted averages, correspondence matching, structural validation) but the REASONING is semantic (trace assembly, proof generation, gap detection, certificate writing). The crystallization boundary falls exactly where it should вҖ” v0.2's expression language forces honesty about which side each cell lives on."

вҠў= obs-proof-carrying-pattern
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "PROOF-CARRYING COMPUTATION AT SCALE: This program is the proof-carrying pattern (rated 9/10 in v0.2 spec) applied to an entire program rather than a single cell. The 'NP work' is generate-proof (LLM synthesizes the argument). The 'P work' is verify-proof-structure (deterministic check: enough steps? all matched? orders differ?). The separation is clean: the LLM does the creative work (finding the proof), the crystallized verifier does the mechanical work (checking the invariants). Neither could do the other's job."

вҠў= obs-maximum-parallelism-window
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "MAXIMUM PARALLELISM WINDOW REVEALS GRAPH STRUCTURE: After frame 0 (input-data frozen), 6 cells become ready simultaneously. This 6-wide parallelism window is the widest in the entire execution. It corresponds to the diamond structure: input-data fans out to 6 independent consumers (2 program-assembly cells + 4 computation cells). The window narrows as dependencies converge toward the single equivalence-certificate. Cell's DAG structure makes parallelism opportunities visible as ready-set width."

вҠў= obs-file-scope-recovery-unused
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "v0.2 FILE-SCOPE RECOVERY NEVER TRIGGERED: All 34 oracle checks passed on first attempt. The file-scope вҠЁ? (retry max 3, partial-accept on exhaustion) was never activated. This is expected: the program operates on small deterministic inputs where oracle satisfaction is near-certain. The recovery policy exists as a safety net for when this program is run on more complex inputs where trace-A/trace-B or generate-proof might produce outputs that fail semantic oracles. The v0.2 file-scope вҠЁ? is insurance, not overhead."

вҠў= obs-verify-split-preserves-trust
  yield observation
  вҠў= observation вҶҗ "SPLITTING VERIFY-PROOF PRESERVES TRUST HIERARCHY: R16 had one verify-proof cell that mixed deterministic and semantic checks, creating a false sense of full crystallization. R17's split makes the trust explicit: verify-proof-structure is TRUSTWORTHY (deterministic, auditable, reproducible) while verify-proof-semantics is TENTATIVE (LLM-dependent, may vary between runs). A consumer of the proof can weight the structural check higher than the semantic check. The v0.2 expression language forced this honesty вҖ” missing-from() was a lie that hid semantic judgment behind a function-call syntax."
